# /test is a real URL that deep-links into the assessment.
# Canonical form is /test (no trailing slash) — that is what the ads, Reddit,
# and blog CTAs use. A trailing-slash visit is normalized to it first.
#   301: /test/ -> /test  (permanent, no loop: different target path)
#   200: /test  -> serve the site root (the SPA shell) WITHOUT changing the URL.
# Target is "/" not "/index.html" on purpose: Cloudflare canonicalizes
# /index.html to /, which would 308-redirect and wipe /test from the URL bar.
# App.jsx reads location.pathname and opens the test intro screen (route
# "intro"). Exact paths only — /api/* Functions and all other assets untouched.
/test/    /test    301
/test     /        200
